  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6583.66 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6590, dealers are currently in positive gamma territory and likely buying this dip as hedging flow. The massive +48.4B gamma wall at 6600 creates a strong magnet effect, while the rapid -17.7% and -25% GEX decay suggests recent positioning unwind that should stabilize price action. Key levels: watch for dealer selling pressure if we push through 6590 flip toward the 6600 wall, while 6550 (-8B gamma) provides downside support where dealers would aggressively buy.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to drift higher toward 6600 with limited downside risk given the strong positive gamma cushion below.",
